A child hospitalized under this chapter shall have the following rights:
The right to due process, as defined in KRS 645.170, within the hospital;
The right to convalescent leave status if appropriate;
The right to be adequately informed as to his individual treatment program;
The right to assist in the planning of his treatment program;
The right to refuse treatment subject to the provisions of KRS 645.170;
The right to maintain and use personal possessions and money;
The right to receive visitors subject to the provisions of KRS 645.170;
The right to receive payment for work performed on behalf of the hospital;
The right to refuse intrusive treatment subject to the provisions of KRS 645.170;
The right to be free from unreasonable use of seclusion and restraint subject to the provisions of KRS 645.170;
The right to seek relief from participating in his treatment plan; and
The right not to be transferred from one (1) facility to another, subject to the provisions of KRS 645.170.
